  <mainContent><![CDATA[<h3>We ensure the safety of all students in a number of different ways:</h3>
<ul>
<li>We require all students to wear lanyards with photo-card ID in order to gain entry onto our campuses</li>
<li>All students have access to our specialist Safeguarding Team who are on hand to support with any issue, including wellbeing and counselling experts</li>
<li>Every member of staff receives regular safeguarding training and raise concerns or report issues relating to safeguarding and welfare</li>
<li>We are committed to creating a culture where British Values are promoted and practised in all aspects of college life, in line with the Government’s counter-terrorism strategy - Prevent</li>
<li>All staff are DBS (Disclosure and Barring Service looking for criminal records) checked; without this approval, staff will not be allowed any access in the college without supervision</li>
<li>The college provides a safe and friendly learning environment compliant with UK Health and Safety legislation</li>
<li>CCTV is installed at various points around the campuses.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Want to find out more?</h3>
<p>If you would like to find out more about how we keep you safe, please view the following policies:</p>
<ul>
<li><a data-udi="umb://document/d35eff9dfff54be7b8821634cecdafea" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d35eff9dfff54be7b8821634cecdafea}" title="Equality &amp; Diversity">Equality &amp; Diversity</a> </li>
<li>Guidance on radicalisation and extremism &lt;page to be added&gt;</li>
<li>Safeguarding Policy &lt;page to be added&gt;</li>
</ul>
<h4>If you would like to discuss anything in more detail, have concerns about your or someone else’s safety please contact our Safeguarding Team on <a href="tel:01268882665" title="Call USP student services">01268 882 665</a> or visit Student Services.</h4>
<p> </p>]]></mainContent>
